11
[h3 id=BeforeWriting 
	" Before writing
	$LF
]h3
[ul 
	[li 
		" Make sure you know what you're talking about.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" If you have to include something off-topic, keep it to a minimum.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Don't shitpost for the sake of shitposting.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Actually read the existing replies first, no need to repeat things.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[h3 id=WhileWriting 
	" While writing
	$LF
]h3
[ul 
	[li 
		" Don't just hit the quote button and start typing. Try to edit the quote so that only important information are contained within.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" When quoting, remove the BBCode (like [img][/img]) around embedded images/videos.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" If you don't care for slightly messy raw text, then do not (put multiple newlines after the [/quote])
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[blockquote 
	"[quote]quoted text[/quote]
	[br 
	]br
	" 
	[br 
	]br
	"your text
	$LF
]blockquote
[ul 
	[li 
		" Instead do (put only a single newline after the [/quote])
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[blockquote 
	"[quote]quoted text[/quote]
	[br 
	]br
	"your text
	$LF
]blockquote
[ul 
	[li 
		" Make sure you provide proper citations for every non-trivial claim you make.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Don't overuse formatting but don't be afraid to use it either.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Never use [center][/center]. It might look good on your screen, but once the window gets bigger it will become really ugly.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Don't embed huge images (in either resolution or filesize). If the resolution can't be reduced, rescale it with something like [img=300x400][/img]. For extra convenience put [url=
		[em 
			"url to image
		]em
		"][/url] around everything. (
		(__wikiLink|displaytext=Example|href=/Forum/Posts/392583)
		")
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" 
		[code 
			"[Ad]
		]code
		" Don't get caught using one of 
		(__wikiLink|displaytext=these arguing techniques|href=/HomePages/Nach/Arguing)
		".
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[h3 id=AfterWriting 
	" After writing
	$LF
]h3
[ul 
	[li 
		" If you notice a mistake, edit your reply and use the 
		[del 
			"overstrike effect
		]del
		" to indicate the change.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Do not edit your reply to include an answer to a later reply. It will screw up the chronology.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" If you want to add content to your 
		[em 
			"reply
		]em
		" immediately after writing it, 
		[b 
			"edit it
		]b
		" instead of making a double post. However, if you want to add content to the 
		[em 
			"topic
		]em
		" itself and your last post was a while ago, then do double post (since edits don't notify people watching the topic).
	]li
]ul
